At least 19 people have been arrested for public violence in the Lwandle area, Western Cape. Disgruntled residents torched rubble and tyres on Monday forcing authorities to close the N2 in the area. According to reports, protesting community members are demanding electricity in the area. It is said that a meeting will be held today between city officials, community leaders and residents, following protests. The situation remains tense in the area. -TNA Reporter   